st.image(image_path, use_column_width=True)
st.write("Harmony is the purposeful arrangement of art elements that results in a cohesive composition. In an artwork that possesses harmony, different art elements complement one another and appear to work together. The other art principle, balance, is closely related to harmony. Balance can create harmony, but an artwork that has harmony might not be balanced. Harmony can be created by the use of similar colors or shapes, and sometimes even contrast as well. For example, an artist may choose a color scheme and repeat a color in this color scheme throughout the composition. After that, the artist might also use contrasting colors to enhance the overall visual appearance and thereby create harmony. Harmony makes an artwork look united, coherent and visually pleasing. It is created in many famous art piece, including Van Goghâ€™s well-known The Starry Night (you can see this painting in the Famous Artwork page).")
